Build a PHP function to change the following array's all values to upper or lower case.

Sample arrays :
$Color = array('A' => 'Blue', 'B' => 'Green', 'c' => 'Red');
Expected Output :
Values are in lower case.
Array ( [A] => blue [B] => green [c] => red )
Values are in upper case.
Array ( [A] => BLUE [B] => GREEN [c] => RED )

SOLUION:
We can achieve this using array_map() along with strtolower() and strtoupper().

CODE:
<?php
function changeCase($array) {
    // Convert values to lowercase
    $lowerArray = array_map('strtolower', $array);

    // Convert values to uppercase
    $upperArray = array_map('strtoupper', $array);

    // Display results
    echo "Values are in lower case.<br>";
    print_r($lowerArray);
    echo "<br><br>";

    echo "Values are in upper case.<br>";
    print_r($upperArray);
}

// Sample array
$Color = array('A' => 'Blue', 'B' => 'Green', 'c' => 'Red');

// Call function
changeCase($Color);
?>


OUTPUT:
Values are in lower case.<br>Array
(
    [A] => blue
    [B] => green
    [c] => red
)
<br><br>Values are in upper case.<br>Array
(
    [A] => BLUE
    [B] => GREEN
    [c] => RED
)
